.TH RESTART-POD 1 "2026-05-26" "SCD Reporting v0.2.0" "SCD Reporting"
.SH NAME
restart-pod \- restart the SCD Reporting web pod in OKD and wait for readiness
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./scripts/restart-pod.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B restart-pod.sh
performs a rolling restart of the
.B web
Deployment in the specified OKD namespace and blocks until the new pod
reaches the
.B Ready
state.
.PP
This is useful after patching a Secret directly (e.g. updating
.BR ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
via
.BR "oc set data" )
or after pushing a new image to Docker Hub with the
.B :latest
tag, when a Helm upgrade is not required.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n " NAMESPACE"
OKD namespace containing the Deployment.
.br
Default:
.B scd-reporting
.TP
.BI \-t " TIMEOUT"
Number of seconds to wait for the pod to become ready before giving up.
.br
Default:
.B 120
.TP
.B \-h
Show a short help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Restart the pod in the default namespace:
.PP
.RS
.EX
./scripts/restart-pod.sh
.EE
.RE
.PP
Restart in a different namespace:
.PP
.RS
.EX
./scripts/restart-pod.sh -n my-namespace
.EE
.RE
.PP
Restart with a longer readiness timeout:
.PP
.RS
.EX
./scripts/restart-pod.sh -t 180
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR build-docker (1),
.BR oc (1)
